                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 42256,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has an opinion to announce."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 3.383,
                        "stop": 352.836,
                        "byte_start": 42256,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 3.383,
                                "stop": 29.643,
                                "byte_start": 42256,
                                "byte_stop": 147268,
                                "text": "This case presents a question of statutory interpretation thus the truth in Lending Act as amended in 1995 caps statutory damages in addition to any proven actual damages and $1,000.00 for violation of the Act\u0027s requirements for consumer loans secured by personal property in this case a motor vehicle."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.643,
                                "stop": 39.691,
                                "byte_start": 147268,
                                "byte_stop": 187496,
                                "text": "The truth and Lending Act instruct lenders to disclose certain information to borrowers and imposes civil liability on lenders who fail to do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.691,
                                "stop": 49.641,
                                "byte_start": 187496,
                                "byte_stop": 227307,
                                "text": "As originally enacted in 1968 the Act set double the amount of the finance charge as statutory damages with this exception."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.641,
                                "stop": 58.123,
                                "byte_start": 227307,
                                "byte_stop": 261266,
                                "text": "For each violation Congress specify the minimum recovery of $100.00 and maximum damages of $1,000.00."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.123,
                                "stop": 78.208,
                                "byte_start": 261266,
                                "byte_stop": 341514,
                                "text": "Congress amended the Act in the 1970\u0027s dividing the statutory damages provision in two clauses: Clause (i) sets statutory damages for long transaction at double the amount of the finance judge, and clause (ii) set damages for lease transactions at 25% of the monthly payment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.208,
                                "stop": 92.886,
                                "byte_start": 341514,
                                "byte_stop": 400238,
                                "text": "Congress retained the $100.00 floor and $1,000.00 dollar ceiling on recovery, and courts consistently held that these limits apply to all consumer financing transactions whether lease or loan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.886,
                                "stop": 109.448,
                                "byte_start": 400238,
                                "byte_stop": 466484,
                                "text": "In 1995, Congress again amended the act by adding a new clause (iii) which increase the limit on recovery but only for violations relating to closed-end mortgage loans commonly home acquisition loans."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 109.448,
                                "stop": 117.615,
                                "byte_start": 466484,
                                "byte_stop": 499190,
                                "text": "In lieu of the $100.00 minimum and $1,000.00 maximum Congress substituted $200.00 and $2,000.00."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.615,
                                "stop": 126.374,
                                "byte_start": 499190,
                                "byte_stop": 534194,
                                "text": "Bradley Nigh the respondent here plaintiff below maintains that the 1995 amendment had a further more dramatic effect."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 126.374,
                                "stop": 131.985,
                                "byte_start": 534194,
                                "byte_stop": 556659,
                                "text": "Elimination of the $1,000.00 cap on damages recoverable under clause (i)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.985,
                                "stop": 144.109,
                                "byte_start": 556659,
                                "byte_stop": 605142,
                                "text": "Nigh attempted to buy a truck from petitioner Koons Buick the financing for the truck well through causing Nigh to lose both that truck and the vehicle Nigh has traded for it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.109,
                                "stop": 157.68,
                                "byte_start": 605142,
                                "byte_stop": 659477,
                                "text": "Nigh commence suit asserting that Koons Buick among other wrongs has violated the Truth in Lending Act by falsely listing a charge of $965.00 for a car alarm Nigh did not order or received."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.68,
                                "stop": 165.714,
                                "byte_start": 659477,
                                "byte_stop": 691555,
                                "text": "A jury returned a verdict ordering Nigh double the amount of the finance charge in dollars approximately $24,000."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 165.714,
                                "stop": 180.545,
                                "byte_start": 691555,
                                "byte_stop": 750905,
                                "text": "The US Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit affirmed that award holding as Nigh urged that the 1995 amendment removed the $1,000.00 cap on recoveries under clause (i) of the statutory damages provision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.545,
                                "stop": 193.209,
                                "byte_start": 750905,
                                "byte_stop": 801583,
                                "text": "We reverse the Court of Appeals judgment and hold that the 1995 amendment left unaltered the $100.00 floor and $1,000.00 ceiling on recoveries under clause (i)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.209,
                                "stop": 215.654,
                                "byte_start": 801583,
                                "byte_stop": 891340,
                                "text": "Less than meticulous drafting of the 1995 amendment created and ambiguity the phrase prescribing the $100.00 floor and $1,000.00 ceiling located at the end of clause (ii) reads, except that liability under this subparagraph shall not be less than $100.00 nor greater than $1,000.00."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 215.654,
                                "stop": 221.06,
                                "byte_start": 891340,
                                "byte_stop": 912969,
                                "text": "Congress ordinarily follows a hierarchical scheme in subdividing statutes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 221.06,
                                "stop": 232.525,
                                "byte_start": 912969,
                                "byte_stop": 958840,
                                "text": "The word subparagraph generally refers to a division preceded by a capital letter the word clause to a division preceded by a lower case roman number."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 232.525,
                                "stop": 241.767,
                                "byte_start": 958840,
                                "byte_stop": 995830,
                                "text": "The three clauses at issue, all in lower case roman numbers, appear in a subparagraph preceded by capital \u0022a\u0022."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 241.767,
                                "stop": 249.99,
                                "byte_start": 995830,
                                "byte_stop": 1028639,
                                "text": "Had congress meant to restrict the $100.00 floor and the $1,000.00 ceiling to clause (ii) of subparagraph \u0022a\u0022?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 249.99,
                                "stop": 260.433,
                                "byte_start": 1028639,
                                "byte_stop": 1070435,
                                "text": "It likely would have flagged that substitute change at least Congress might have stated in clause (ii) liability under this clause."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 260.433,
                                "stop": 271.167,
                                "byte_start": 1070435,
                                "byte_stop": 1113381,
                                "text": "The statutory history cast lie down on Congress\u0027s meaning the $100.00 floor and $1,000.00 ceiling from the start have applied to loans in the clause (i) category."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 271.167,
                                "stop": 281.879,
                                "byte_start": 1113381,
                                "byte_stop": 1156221,
                                "text": "The new clause (iii) removes closed-end mortgage loans from clause (i)\u0027s governance only to the extent that clause (iii) raises the minimum and maximum recoveries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 281.879,
                                "stop": 295.642,
                                "byte_start": 1156221,
                                "byte_stop": 1211288,
                                "text": "There is scant indication that by raising the minimum and maximum recoveries for mainly home acquisition mortgage loans Congress meant thereby to repeal the dollar limitation on all other loans."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 295.642,
                                "stop": 311.135,
                                "byte_start": 1211288,
                                "byte_stop": 1273250,
                                "text": "We therefore conclude that the $100.00 floor and $1,000.00 ceiling continue to apply to recoveries for Truth In Lending Act violations involving loans described in clause (i) and leases described in clause (ii)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 311.135,
                                "stop": 321.066,
                                "byte_start": 1273250,
                                "byte_stop": 1312956,
                                "text": "Indicating the large interest the statutory construction case has generated Justice Stevens has filed a concurring opinion in which Justice Breyer joins."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 321.066,
                                "stop": 352.836,
                                "byte_start": 1312956,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Kennedy has filed a concurring opinion in which the Chief Justice joins; Justice Thomas has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment, and Justice Scalia has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
